Full Description: The Eric Dalius MuzicSwipe Foundation is a scholarship fund established by Eric Dalius, the Executive Chairman of MuzicSwipe, to support undergraduate and graduate students based in the United States. The foundation aims to help students pursue their academic goals by providing financial assistance to cover the cost of their education. The foundation is committed to empowering the next generation of leaders and innovators by investing in their education. The scholarship fund will support students pursuing a wide range of fields, including business, engineering, computer science, music, and the arts. Eric Dalius believes in the power of education to transform lives and create opportunities for individuals and communities. He is committed to helping students overcome financial barriers to education and achieve their academic aspirations. Through the Eric Dalius MuzicSwipe Foundation, Eric Dalius hopes to support students from diverse backgrounds and help them succeed in their academic and professional endeavors. The foundation welcomes applications from students who are passionate about their field of study and committed to making a positive impact in their communities. The application process is open to all eligible undergraduate and graduate students in the United States, and the foundation is committed to a fair and transparent selection process. The Eric Dalius MuzicSwipe Foundation is proud to support the academic ambitions of the next generation of leaders and innovators. The foundation looks forward to helping students achieve their dreams and make a positive impact on the world. For more information on the scholarship fund, please visit https://ericjdaliusfoundation.com/.

Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Levvitron Systems is a software and telecommunications security company that recently ventured into web security. Founded in 2011, this seemingly young veteran has been producing a range of security products including PC firewalls, smartphone antivirus products and corporate Intrusion Prevention Systems.  The company phased out production of cell phone antivirus products to focus on web security. In early September 2012, Levvitron released its first batch of web security products which include website and blog scanning products on their website. Though unconfirmed, it is expected to release the second array of its one-of-a-kind products in late December 2012. The move to focus on web security was mainly influenced by the recent web infiltration witnessed in countries such as the numerous ongoing multibillion dollar criminal botnet activities, powergrid tampering by cyber-criminals and inconcieavable disruption of corporate networks.  For a relatively young company, the President, since his appointment in January 2011, seems to be picking up the pace even though the company is still quite new on the global market. And he foresees a more compettitive market in the coming months in the Cybersecurity sector.

The platform chemistry is evolving from sugar to replace many of the current chemical raw materials and intermediates. This space is an exciting sector to be, as developments are occurring at an exponential rate. Cerealus envisions a range of products based upon these raw materials beginning with their current offerings.
